per around Eclipse Sisu/Guice; its normal core usage is in-process dependency injection, class-space scanning, and bean location using transitive Maven dependencies already brought in by org.sonatype.sisu:sisu-inject-bean:2.4.1. The observed javac failure is an API/signature drift in the existing test, not a missing dependency, Docker service, or environment/system property.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact declares optional integrations for slf4j, OSGi, JUnit 4, and TestNG; tests that deliberately exercise those optional surfaces may need additional dependencies, but they are not required for meaningful core coverage.\",\n    \"The library is a legacy/deprecated compatibility wrapper over Eclipse Sisu APIs, so generated tests should verify method signatures against the resolved 2.4.1 artifact rather than assuming the 2.4.0 test API still matches.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_046377f33d62a12a016a3e6933d4f881959aa9b0e5162f39fa\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5216, "output": 1109, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36021, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782475044818, "responseId": "resp_046377f33d62a12a016a3e69255dfc8195b593a8aafc1b3dd9"}}
